        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Cloud application portability remains unrealistic</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      Cloud portability once seemed like a groundbreaking advancement in the digital infrastructure landscape. Initial expectations were high with the launch of Amazon S3 in 2006 and similar services. Providers promised the ability to migrate workloads across different service providers seamlessly.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2024/09/03/cloud-application-portability-remains-unrealistic/"  >(Info World)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
<div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Thu, 05 Sep 2024 21:31:37 GMT">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Thu, 05 Sep 2024 21:31:37 GMT">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Network World">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static9/tech/2024/09/05/edgecore-unveils-high-performance-400g-spine-switch-for-data-centers.webp" alt="Edgecore unveils high-performance 400G spine switch for data centers" itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Edgecore unveils high-performance 400G spine switch for data centers</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      Edgecore Networks is taking the wraps off its latest data center networking hardware, the 400G-optimized DCS511 spine switch.
The DCS511 is built around the Broadcom Tomahawk 4 chipset and provides a total switching capacity of 12.8 Terabits per second.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2024/09/05/edgecore-unveils-high-performance-400g-spine-switch-for-data-centers/"  >(Network World)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
<div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Tue, 03 Sep 2024 15:49:19 GMT">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Tue, 03 Sep 2024 15:49:19 GMT">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Computer World">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
