    <h3 itemprop="headline">Trump lawyers fight to overturn jury's finding that he sexually abused E. Jean Carroll</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      NEW YORK (AP) — While Donald Trump campaigns for the presidency, his lawyers are fighting to overturn a verdict finding him liable for sexual abuse and slander. Three judges of the 2nd U.S.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/politics/2024/09/06/trump-lawyers-fight-to-overturn-jurys-finding-that-he-sexually-abused-e-jean-carroll/"  >(Associated Press, PIX 11)</a>
    </p>
