<div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Thu, 05 Sep 2024 09:05:00 GMT">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Thu, 05 Sep 2024 09:05:00 GMT">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Carrie Johnson, MPR News">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static9/politics/2024/09/05/npr-trump-election-case-jack-smith-immunity.webp" alt="Trump Jan. 6 case gets its first hearing since the Supreme Court's immunity ruling" itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Trump Jan. 6 case gets its first hearing since the Supreme Court's immunity ruling</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      Lawyers for the government's special counsel and former President Donald Trump are set to clash in court in Washington over how the election interference case against him will proceed.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/politics/2024/09/05/npr-trump-election-case-jack-smith-immunity/"  >(Carrie Johnson, MPR News)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
<div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Fri, 06 Sep 2024 03:34:52 GMT">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Fri, 06 Sep 2024 03:34:52 GMT">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Rich Johnson, NewsNation">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static9/politics/2024/09/06/trump-to-appear-at-hearing-sources.webp" alt="Trump to appear at E. Jean Carroll hearing: Sources" itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Trump to appear at E. Jean Carroll hearing: Sources</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      A jury found Trump liable in the civil sexual abuse case and the panel awarded E. Jean Carroll a total of $5 million.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/politics/2024/09/06/trump-to-appear-at-hearing-sources/"  >(Rich Johnson, NewsNation)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
</div><div class="column vcwi"><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Sun, 08 Sep 2024 03:06:52 GMT">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Sun, 08 Sep 2024 03:06:52 GMT">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="MORIAH BALINGIT, Associated Press, KGET 17, NBC">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static9/politics/2024/09/08/walz-touts-democratic-record-of-defending-lgbtq-rights-says-harris-will-advance-cause-if-elected.webp" alt="Walz touts Democratic record of defending LGBTQ+ rights, says Harris will advance cause if elected" itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Walz touts Democratic record of defending LGBTQ+ rights, says Harris will advance cause if elected</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      WASHINGTON (AP) — Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz touted Vice President Kamala Harris' record of defending LGBTQ+ rights on Saturday night, pledging to a supportive crowd that she will advance their cause if elected president.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/politics/2024/09/08/walz-touts-democratic-record-of-defending-lgbtq-rights-says-harris-will-advance-cause-if-elected/"  >(MORIAH BALINGIT, Associated Press, KGET 17, NBC)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
